infos.info: 1925-90's heard on WSM, local Nashville radio, up to four hours. - By Hickerson, the program was aka WSM Barn Dance until 10/10/27 and aka Pet Milk Show 1959-1961 when it was sponsored by Pet Milk. - -------------------------------------------------- - The network portion of the show was sponsored by Prince Albert. The non-network portion was various sponsors like Schick, Kellogg's, Coca-Cola, Lava, and Pet Milk, among others. - -------------------------------------------------- - Originally from WSM (Nashville) studio (65 minutes, The WSM Barn Dance in 1926 became the Opry) - Source: The Big Broadcast, Frank Buxton and Bill Owen - --------------------------------------------------
